To: Lauren Heath
Cc: Laura Bradley, Michelle Black

Lauren,

A short update on where the investor relations program for Castaneda, Adams a=
nd Davis stands, and one thing we could use from your side. We are still earl=
y, but the shape of the work is set and the pieces are moving in the right or=
der. Nothing here needs action today; I mainly want you to be looking at the =
same picture we are.

Laura Bradley has the first cut of the core messaging drafted off the kickoff=
 conversation, and Michelle Black is assembling the proof points behind each =
line so nothing in the story rests on a figure we cannot stand behind. Our pl=
an is to get the messaging framework to you next week for a first read, well =
before any of it points toward an announcement. I would rather you push back =
on the language now, when it costs a redraft, than after it has traveled.

The one ask for now is thirty minutes with you and whoever owns the numbers o=
n the Castaneda, Adams and Davis side, so we hear the investor concerns in yo=
ur own words before the language hardens. Send me a couple of windows that wo=
rk this week or next and I will set it up.

Best,
Michael Morris


